{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F7DVDKARxhTfm9Up1CpfuK","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# seed-storage — environment variable reference\n2\t# Copy to .env and fill in values. Never commit .env.\n3\t#\n4\t# Credentials injected by ant-keeper use file-mode (PATH variants).\n5\t# All PATH vars point to files containing the raw secret; the file is read at startup.\n6\t\n7\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n8\t# Neo4j — graph database\n9\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n10\t\n11\t# Bolt connection URI (K8s: NodePort 30687)\n12\tNEO4J_URI=bolt://neo4j.ant-keeper.svc:7687\n13\t\n14\t# Neo4j username (default: neo4j)\n15\tNEO4J_USER=neo4j\n16\t\n17\t# Neo4j password — set directly OR via file path (ant-keeper file-mode)\n18\tNEO4J_PASSWORD=\n19\tNEO4J_PASSWORD_PATH=\n20\t\n21\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n22\t# Redis — queue, dedup, rate-limit, circuit breaker, cost tracking\n23\t# DB 2 is reserved for seed-storage (DB 0 = ant-keeper, avoid collision)\n24\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n25\t\n26\tREDIS_URL=redis://redis.ant-keeper.svc:6379/2\n27\t\n28\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n29\t# Discord bot — ingestion source\n30\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n31\t\n32\t# Bot token — set directly OR via file path (ant-keeper file-mode)\n33\tDISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=\n34\tDISCORD_BOT_TOKEN_PATH=\n35\t\n36\t# Comma-separated list of Discord channel IDs to monitor\n37\t# Example: DISCORD_CHANNEL_IDS=123456789012345678,987654321098765432\n38\tDISCORD_CHANNEL_IDS=\n39\t\n40\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n41\t# Discord alerts webhook — circuit breaker / budget / dead-letter alerts\n42\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n43\t\n44\t# Webhook URL — set directly OR via file path (ant-keeper file-mode)\n45\tDISCORD_ALERTS_WEBHOOK_URL=\n46\tDISCORD_ALERTS_WEBHOOK_PATH=\n47\t\n48\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n49\t# LLM provider\n50\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n51\t\n52\t# Provider: openai | anthropic | groq  (default: openai)\n53\tLLM_PROVIDER=openai\n54\t\n55\t# OpenAI — required for embeddings regardless of LLM_PROVIDER\n56\tOPENAI_API_KEY=\n57\t\n58\t# Anthropic (only needed if LLM_PROVIDER=anthropic)\n59\tANTHROPIC_API_KEY=\n60\t\n61\t# Groq (only needed if LLM_PROVIDER=groq)\n62\tGROQ_API_KEY=\n63\t\n64\t# LLM model name (default: gpt-4o-mini for openai)\n65\tLLM_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini\n66\t\n67\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n68\t# Vision provider — for image resolver\n69\t# Defaults to LLM_PROVIDER when not set.\n70\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n71\t\n72\tVISION_PROVIDER=\n73\t\n74\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n75\t# Transcription backend — for video/audio resolver\n76\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n77\t\n78\t# Backend: whisper | assemblyai  (default: whisper)\n79\tTRANSCRIPTION_BACKEND=whisper\n80\t\n81\t# AssemblyAI (only needed if TRANSCRIPTION_BACKEND=assemblyai)\n82\tASSEMBLYAI_API_KEY=\n83\t\n84\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n85\t# GitHub (optional) — for github resolver\n86\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n87\t\n88\tGITHUB_TOKEN=\n89\tGITHUB_TOKEN_PATH=\n90\t\n91\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n92\t# Budget / expansion limits\n93\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n94\t\n95\t# Hard daily LLM spend ceiling in USD. Exceeded → graph_ingest queue pauses.\n96\tDAILY_LLM_BUDGET=5.00\n97\t\n98\t# Maximum frontier expansion depth (0 = direct link from message)\n99\tHARD_DEPTH_CEILING=5\n100\t\n101\t# Maximum child URLs extracted per resolved content\n102\tMAX_EXPANSION_BREADTH=20\n103\t\n104\t# Enable automatic frontier scanning via Celery beat (default: false)\n105\tFRONTIER_AUTO_ENABLED=false\n106\t\n107\t# Max add_episode() calls per minute across all workers\n108\tRATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE=100\n109\t\n110\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n111\t# Celery worker concurrency\n112\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n113\t\n114\tWORKER_CONCURRENCY_RAW=2\n115\tWORKER_CONCURRENCY_GRAPH=4\n116\t\n117\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n118\t# API / Health\n119\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n120\t\n121\t# FastAPI app (legacy, kept for backwards compat)\n122\tAPI_HOST=0.0.0.0\n123\tAPI_PORT=7860\n124\t\n125\t# Health endpoint (supervisord process)\n126\tHEALTH_PORT=8080\n127\t\n128\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n129\t# Logging\n130\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n131\t\n132\t# Log level: DEBUG | INFO | WARNING | ERROR  (default: INFO)\n133\tLOG_LEVEL=INFO\n134\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"57251451-71b9-447a-8e1e-4d99539adbf5","uuid":"38c83ee8-a143-4268-8a06-5031f755497f","timestamp":"2026-04-19T02:28:59.854Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/wyler-zahm/Desktop/cruse-control/seed-storage-forge/.env.example","content":"# seed-storage — environment variable reference\n# Copy to .env and fill in values. Never commit .env.\n#\n# Credentials injected by ant-keeper use file-mode (PATH variants).\n# All PATH vars point to files containing the raw secret; the file is read at startup.\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Neo4j — graph database\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Bolt connection URI (K8s: NodePort 30687)\nNEO4J_URI=bolt://neo4j.ant-keeper.svc:7687\n\n# Neo4j username (default: neo4j)\nNEO4J_USER=neo4j\n\n# Neo4j password — set directly OR via file path (ant-keeper file-mode)\nNEO4J_PASSWORD=\nNEO4J_PASSWORD_PATH=\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Redis — queue, dedup, rate-limit, circuit breaker, cost tracking\n# DB 2 is reserved for seed-storage (DB 0 = ant-keeper, avoid collision)\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nREDIS_URL=redis://redis.ant-keeper.svc:6379/2\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Discord bot — ingestion source\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Bot token — set directly OR via file path (ant-keeper file-mode)\nDISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=\nDISCORD_BOT_TOKEN_PATH=\n\n# Comma-separated list of Discord channel IDs to monitor\n# Example: DISCORD_CHANNEL_IDS=123456789012345678,987654321098765432\nDISCORD_CHANNEL_IDS=\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Discord alerts webhook — circuit breaker / budget / dead-letter alerts\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Webhook URL — set directly OR via file path (ant-keeper file-mode)\nDISCORD_ALERTS_WEBHOOK_URL=\nDISCORD_ALERTS_WEBHOOK_PATH=\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# LLM provider\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Provider: openai | anthropic | groq  (default: openai)\nLLM_PROVIDER=openai\n\n# OpenAI — required for embeddings regardless of LLM_PROVIDER\nOPENAI_API_KEY=\n\n# Anthropic (only needed if LLM_PROVIDER=anthropic)\nANTHROPIC_API_KEY=\n\n# Groq (only needed if LLM_PROVIDER=groq)\nGROQ_API_KEY=\n\n# LLM model name (default: gpt-4o-mini for openai)\nLLM_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Vision provider — for image resolver\n# Defaults to LLM_PROVIDER when not set.\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nVISION_PROVIDER=\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Transcription backend — for video/audio resolver\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Backend: whisper | assemblyai  (default: whisper)\nTRANSCRIPTION_BACKEND=whisper\n\n# AssemblyAI (only needed if TRANSCRIPTION_BACKEND=assemblyai)\nASSEMBLYAI_API_KEY=\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# GitHub (optional) — for github resolver\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nGITHUB_TOKEN=\nGITHUB_TOKEN_PATH=\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Budget / expansion limits\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Hard daily LLM spend ceiling in USD. Exceeded → graph_ingest queue pauses.\nDAILY_LLM_BUDGET=5.00\n\n# Maximum frontier expansion depth (0 = direct link from message)\nHARD_DEPTH_CEILING=5\n\n# Maximum child URLs extracted per resolved content\nMAX_EXPANSION_BREADTH=20\n\n# Enable automatic frontier scanning via Celery beat (default: false)\nFRONTIER_AUTO_ENABLED=false\n\n# Max add_episode() calls per minute across all workers\nRATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE=100\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Celery worker concurrency\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nWORKER_CONCURRENCY_RAW=2\nWORKER_CONCURRENCY_GRAPH=4\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# API / Health\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# FastAPI app (legacy, kept for backwards compat)\nAPI_HOST=0.0.0.0\nAPI_PORT=7860\n\n# Health endpoint (supervisord process)\nHEALTH_PORT=8080\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Logging\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Log level: DEBUG | INFO | WARNING | ERROR  (default: INFO)\nLOG_LEVEL=INFO\n","numLines":134,"startLine":1,"totalLines":134}}}
